title: Say's law and building products 
---
I got into a slight disagreement with a co-worker (a superior of mine, really) about supply-generated demand today. 

To be fair, I wouldn't exactly call the exchange an argument, since, for one, I'm not sure he disagreed with me -- and I certainly didn't completely disagree with him -- and it all ended in aporia anyway. We were discussing building a new product, and in general, most conversations about what we build end up sorting team members into two camps: 
1. Those that believe we should focus on "blocking and tackling", building the critical pieces of functionality needed to ship the product. 
